Honey, Cinnamon, and Walnut Rugelach (Rogaliki)
  --Julia Frey of Vikalinka

Dough:
3 c (350g) ap flour + extra for rolling
1 c (250ml) sour cream
3/4 c (150g) butter
1 tsp vanilla

Preheat oven to 350F/180C and line baking sheets with parchment paper. Whip softened butter together with sour cream in a large bowl. Add flour in small portions and continue mixing. Empty contents onto floured worksurface and continue kneading until you have smooth, pliable dough, adding flour if sticky. Cover and let sit for 10 min.

Filling:
1 1/2 c (190g) chopped walnuts
1 c (200g) sugar
1/4 c (60ml) honey
1 tsp cinnamon
1 egg for brushing

Mix nuts with sugar and cinnamon and set aside. Make sure honey is spreadable, heating if needed.

Divide dough into 4 parts and roll out each individually into a circle, dough should be ~1 cm. Brush honey on it and divide into 8 or 16 even triangles. Sprinkle 1/4 of the nut mix on a circle. Roll up each triangle starting from the wide end towards the center of the circle. Arrange on prepared baking sheets, brush with egg wash and bak for 25-30 min.
